Russia Signs Afghan Helicopter Deal With U.S., Kommersant Says

-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 
2011-05-28T08:49:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/russia-signs-afghan-helicopter-deal-with-u-s-kommersant-says.html
Russia and the  United States  signed
an agreement to sell 21 Mi-17V5 transport helicopters to
 Afghanistan , Kommersant reported.    Russia will ship the first nine helicopters to Kabul this
year and the remaining 12 in 2012, the Moscow-based newspaper
reported, citing a statement from the Federal Service for
Military-Technical Cooperation.  The deal may be worth over $300
million, according to people with knowledge of the transaction,
Kommersant reported.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
